=Contextual Quote=

"Now underway east of Suez, where data centres are built beside hydropower dams, and moral education still matters because coherence is a civic resource. There, the “right to exit” is less compelling than the duty to maintain.  ... (They) understand coherence as infrastructure. They know that legitimacy flows through pipes before it flows through code. Their “popups” are pilot zones; their “founders” are cadres; their “venture capital” is municipal surplus. The electro-state doesn’t dream of starting over — it dreams of scaling up gracefully."

- Chor Pharn [https://thecuttingfloor.substack.com/p/popups-and-pipes-how-the-network]


